This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as abstractive summarization and machine translation. It also introduces a strategy to manipulate the behavior of a neural decoder, which is a common technique used in NLP. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a model that uses an interpolation of the actor and critic for decision making, which is a common technique in reinforcement learning. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with improving the performance of neural decoders, which is a common task in AI research. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the proposed strategy could potentially be applied to image captioning tasks, which is a common task in computer vision. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural decoders and proposes a strategy to improve their performance.
